J. Michael Nixon  Non-Executive Director, Installed Building Products, Inc.AgeTotal Calculated CompensationThis person is connected to 1 Board Members in 1 different organizations across 1 different industries.See Board Relationships72$275,205
Background

		Mr. J. Michael Nixon is the Founder of TCI Contracting, LLC and has been its Chief Executive Officer since 2006. Mr. Nixon has been President and Co-Owner of Q.I. Corporation, a building materials contractor, since 1967. He is the Owner of Hawks Ridge Golf Club in Ball Ground, Georgia. Prior to TCI Contracting, LLC, he founded and led Quality Insulation Inc. He has extensive experience and leadership in the building products installation industry. He has been a Non-Executive ... Director of Installed Building Products, Inc. since December 2012. He served as a Director of Flooring America Inc., since February 1996. In 2010, he was appointed to the Cherokee County Airport Authority and in 2011, Mr. Nixon was appointed to the Georgia Properties Commission.Read Full Background




