Michael Nixon's Biography



Mr. Nixon is the founder of TCI Contracting, LLC, an installer of building products and one of our subsidiaries, where he has served as the Chief Executive Officer since 2006. Prior to establishing TCI Contracting, LLC, Mr. Nixon founded and led Quality Insulation Inc., a Connecticut-based insulation installer, over a 30-year period. He is the owner of Hawks Ridge Golf Club in Ball Ground, Georgia. In 2010, Mr. Nixon was appointed to the Cherokee County Airport Authority, and in 2011, he was appointed to the Georgia Properties Commission. Mr. Nixon attended Memphis State University. Mr. Nixon's extensive experience and leadership in the build ...
(Read More)

			Mr. Nixon is the founder of TCI Contracting, LLC, an installer of building products and one of our subsidiaries, where he has served as the Chief Executive Officer since 2006. Prior to establishing TCI Contracting, LLC, Mr. Nixon founded and led Quality Insulation Inc., a Connecticut-based insulation installer, over a 30-year period. He is the owner of Hawks Ridge Golf Club in Ball Ground, Georgia. In 2010, Mr. Nixon was appointed to the Cherokee County Airport Authority, and in 2011, he was appointed to the Georgia Properties Commission. Mr. Nixon attended Memphis State University. Mr. Nixon's extensive experience and leadership in the building products installation industry make him a valued member of the Board.
		
Source: Installed Building Products, Inc. on 04/21/2017
		
	

 






