Director of Installed Building Products (NYSE:IBP), Nixon J Michael, sells 6,140 shares worth $307,000
According to Installed Building Products's most recent Form 4 filing with the SEC dated Mar 03 07:55 PM, company Director, Nixon J Michael disclosed selling 6,140 shares at a cost of $50.00. At the time of this transaction (Mar 01), this trade was worth $307,000 in total. As of Mar 01, Nixon J Michael now owns 1,667,518 shares in total worth about $82,792,268.7. 
For the last few recent trades made by Installed Building Products (NYSE:IBP) Director, Nixon J Michael, we have the following information:




SEC Form 4 filing: Mar 02: Sold 8,804 shares at the rate of $50.00 per share. Total worth of this trade was $440,200. Total number of shares owned as of Mar 02 were 1,658,714
SEC Form 4 filing: Feb 27: Sold 50,000 shares at the rate of $45.00 per share. Total worth of this trade was $2,250,000. Total number of shares owned as of Feb 27 were 1,723,658
SEC Form 4 filing: Feb 28: Sold 50,000 shares at the rate of $47.05 per share. Total worth of this trade was $2,352,485. Total number of shares owned as of Feb 28 were 1,673,658




